│ The `ofmin_pred_ty` and `ufmin_pred_ty` structures define the predicates for ordered    │
│ and unordered floating-point minimum comparisons, respectively. These are used in the   │
│ `m_OrdOrUnordFMin` matcher to identify patterns in the IR that correspond to            │
│ floating-point minimum operations.                                                      │
│                                                                                         │
│ The `ofmin_pred_ty` matches ordered less-than (`FCMP_OLT`) and ordered                  │
│ less-than-or-equal (`FCMP_OLE`) comparisons, while the `ufmin_pred_ty` matches          │
│ unordered less-than (`FCMP_ULT`) and unordered less-than-or-equal (`FCMP_ULE`)          │
│ comparisons.                                                                            │
│                                                                                         │
