│ The `replaceInstUsesWith` function replaces all uses of an instruction with a new       │
│ value. It also ensures that the worklist is updated with the users of the replaced      │
│ instruction. This function is used in the `visitSelectInst` function to replace a       │
│ `select` instruction with the `llvm.minnum` intrinsic.                                  │
│                                                                                         │
│ The issue likely arises from the transformation logic in `visitSelectInst`, where the   │
│ `select` instruction is replaced with the `llvm.minnum` intrinsic without properly      │
│ handling the signed zero case. This can lead to incorrect behavior when the input       │
│ values include `+0.0` and `-0.0`.                                                       │
│                                                                                         │
│ To confirm this, I will inspect the logic in `visitSelectInst` that creates the         │
│ `llvm.minnum` intrinsic and check if it accounts for the signed zero case.              │
